Well, a lotta ppl have been requesting this one for a long long time now. So I
finally decided to sit down and finish this once and for all.
Simple. It's the one and only Floodster for MSN Messenger. Does any1 ever
you on MSN? Do u want to annoy some1 on MSN? Well, simply use this tool.
A flooder is something that sends out multiple messages simultaneously,
you ever doing anything (apart from a few clicks). A flooder can ALSO allow a
person to get disconnected (if the guy has a cheap modem).
Oooh, I could have made this a simple one, but I noticed that the MSN Instant
Message windows have built in anti-flooding
schemes. So the same text over the same time or in a short time over and over
again can cause the MSN Messenger client to stop sending the packets.
So....I made multiple-messages into it with varied intervals -- all which you can
set! (Weeehaaaaaa.) In other words, this means GUARANTEED flooding. :)
Another feature of this is that you can do multiple flooding. YES! Flood more
Ooh ya, did I mention you can also email bomb the user(s)? :) :)
HOW CAN I USE THE INSTANT MESSAGE FLOODER?
Where it says: "Select the online person from the list.", simply select the nicks
from there (you can do multiple selections by holding down shift or ctrl or both).
You type in the message in the message text boxes (how many messages you
depend on the number you specified in the Options Dialog). And finally press
HOW CAN U USE THE EMAIL BOMBER?
First, press the "Email Bomber" button at the top. Now, type the name of the
person you want to bomb and press the "Add the above >>" button. All the
email addresses that you add to the list are bombed. Type in the message in
message text boxes (how many messages you use will depend on the number
you specified in the Options Dialog -- however, if you did not choose custom
text invitation type mail, you will not be able to write into these textboxes). Press
the "Send" button and all the email addresses that you added to the list will be
HOW CAN I SET THE OPTIONS?
The options may be a little confusing. Okay, starting from the top to the bottom:
"How many messages to use?" -- this will set the number of messages that you
will use so that the messages differ in the flooding and MSN does not detect
that you are flooding. It also sets of how many messages you want to use for
the custom text used in the Email Bomber so that each mail will have a different
text. Keep this option with the highest number possible to ensure good
"Randomly send messages?" -- this will allow the flooding to choose from a
random message you have typed each time it floods. Better variation results in
"Type of email:" -- with this you can set the type of emails you want to send. A
normal invitation mail does not include any messages writing by you but is
faster. However, a custom invitation mail is vice versa.
"How many interval values?" -- this will allow you to set how many interval
values you want to use. More interval values means more variation between
the timing of each flood message so that MSN doesn't detect the flooding.
"Interval values:" -- set the interval values. This cannot be blank or alphabetic
(duh!). 1000 means 1 second of interval, 2000 means 2 seconds of interval.
TIP: It is better to use above 500 or things get screwy.
"Randomly use intervals?" -- like the random messages, this option will allow
the program to pick an interval value from any of the values you have specified
and use that between each flood message.
"Flood Option:" -- this allows you to set whether you want to stop the flooding
by pressing the stop button or you want it to stop after sending a specific
number of floods (you can stop the flooding by pressing the stop button even
when you have specified a number of floods).
"How many times to flood:" -- if you specified a number of times to flood, you
have to enter a value here.
WARNING: USE AT YOUR OWN RISK!
